title: TripKitchen at TripSpace
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, Indian, Western, Mediterranean, Beer/Wine, Take-out, Asian, English, European, Fusion, Middle Eastern, Non-veg
description: Serves meat, veg options available. Lovely space underneath the railway arches near Haggerston Overground station and Regent's Canal. Part of a yoga and dance studio. Serves mainly vegetarian and vegan dishes, with some meat and fish specials a few times a week. The menu focuses a lot on Middle Eastern and Indian cuisine. Open for breakfast, lunch and dinner, plus a weekend brunch with a small selection of cakes, some of which are vegan and/or gluten free, and raw nut and date balls.
